#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Gwiti Ha’atel was born the son of some poor farmer in northern Wesnoth and "
"grew up amidst the barren land with his elder brother, Nati. Their parents "
"saved their money little by little and enrolled Gwiti and Nati at the Royal "
"Medical Academy outside of Weldyn. In this way, they attempted to lift their "
"sons out of poverty and hardship; Gwiti specialized in pharmacology and "
"restorative magic, and Nati focused primarily on surgery, and both excelled "
"in their respective fields. It was clear to anyone who saw them that they "
"would become one of the great physicians."
msgstr ""
"Gwiti Ha’atel は Wesnoth 北部の貧しい農夫の息子として生まれ、兄の Nati と共"
"に、荒れた土地の中で育ちました。彼らの両親は、少しずつ金を貯め、Gwiti と "
"Nati を Weldyn 郊外にある王立医学アカデミーに入学させました。そうする事で息子"
"達を、貧しく苦しい生活から抜け出させようと試みたのです。Gwiti は薬学と回復魔"
"法を、Nati は主に外科を専門に学び、それぞれ優秀な成績を保ちました。彼らが偉大"
"な医者の一人になる事は誰の目から見ても明らかでした。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Ironically, however, their fate was the opposite of peaceful: in 1094 YW, "
"just as they were about to complete their training and take their first "
"steps as physicians, the Black Plague swept through Wesnoth. This calamity "
"claimed many victims, regardless of wealth or poverty. Even the parents of "
"Gwiti and Nati were ravaged by the dreaded disease.\n"
"\n"
"The two Ha’atel tried to save their parents with their own knowledge. "
"However, they came face-to-face with their inexperience and helplessness at "
"the same time. As their parents’ condition slowly but clearly worsened, Nati "
"began to despair of the passing of time. Gwiti, on the other hand, "
"frantically gathered through magical tomes and searched for methods to save "
"his parents’ future."
msgstr ""
"しかし、皮肉な事に、彼らの運命は平穏とは真逆でした。Wesnoth 歴 1094 年、彼ら"
"が修業を終え、医者としての一歩を踏み出そうとした矢先、Wesnoth を黒死病が襲い"
"ました。貧富の差に関係なく、この天災は多くの犠牲を生み出しました。そして "
"Gwiti と Nati の両親も、この恐ろしい病に蝕まれました。\n"
"\n"
"二人の Ha’atel は自分達の知識によって両親を救おうとしました。しかし彼らは自分"
"たちの経験不足と無力さを同時に知りました。両親の病状が徐々に、しかし明らかに"
"悪化する中で、Nati は時の流れに絶望し始めました。一方 Gwiti は、死に物狂いで"
"魔法の書物をかき集め、両親の未来を救う方法を探しました。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The last tome Gwiti reached was the journal written by one of the fallen "
"sorcerers. He studied its decaying readings and devoted all his efforts to "
"mastering its magic. Ultimately, Gwiti completed an immortality spell that "
"would anchor the lives of his parents to this world forever. Just before "
"performing his ritual, however, Nati noticed Gwiti’s suspicious behavior. He "
"denounced Gwiti’s attempt as an act against the natural order of things. And "
"while they were arguing, their parents’ condition suddenly changed, and they "
"soon fell into eternal sleep."
msgstr ""
"Gwiti の最後に到達した書物は、堕落した魔法使いの一人が記した手記でした。彼は"
"その朽ちた読み物を研究し、全ての労力を注ぎ込み、その魔法を習得しました。最終"
"的に、Gwiti は両親の命をこの世界に永遠に固定する、不老不死の呪文を完成させま"
"した。しかし、その儀式を行う直前に、Nati が Gwiti の不審な行動に気付きまし"
"た。彼は Gwiti の試みを、自然の摂理に反する行為として非難しました。そして、二"
"人が口論している途中、兄弟の両親の容体は急変し、やがて命を落としました。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:31
msgid ""
"After the death of their parents, Gwiti severed all ties with his brother; "
"he firmly believed that, had Nati not intervened, their parents would have "
"survived. With no other option to calm his mind, Gwiti abandoned his smile, "
"his happiness, and resolved to live on his lonesome. Perhaps it was this "
"resolve that led him to volunteer as an army physician, and he began his "
"path of constant commitment to the front lines of battle."
msgstr ""
"両親の死後、Gwiti は彼の兄弟と一切の関係を断ちました。Nati の介入がなければ、"
"両親は必ず生き延びていたはずだと、彼は固く信じました。そう思う他に気持ちを落"
"ち着かせる選択肢はありませんでした。Gwiti は笑顔を捨て、幸せを捨て、自分だけ"
"の力で生きる事を決意しました。その決意が関係したのか、彼は軍医に志願し、戦場"
"に常に身を投じる道を歩み始めました。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, Nati remained concerned for Gwiti, who wished to lead the life "
"that had lost its human warmth. At the same time, Nati had been thinking for "
"some time about the book, the root of all their misfortunes, which he had "
"taken from Gwiti’s hands and sealed away. Then, several months after the "
"tragedy, he flipped through the pages of the tome in torment. It was the "
"fatal mistake for Nati. At that moment, his spirit was simultaneously "
"invaded by the traces of Gwiti’s experiments and the insidious curse that "
"clung to the very essence of the tome..."
msgstr ""
"一方、Nati は、人間としての温かさを失った人生を望む Gwiti の事を心配に思って"
"いました。同時に、Nati は自らが Gwiti の手から奪い、封じ込めた、全ての元凶と"
"なったあの書物について、しばらく考えていました。そして、悲劇から数か月経った"
"頃、思い悩んだ彼は、その書のページをふと捲りました。それは Nati にとって致命"
"的な失敗でした。その時、彼の精神に、Gwiti の残した実験の痕跡、そして書物にこ"
"びり付いた陰湿な呪いが同時に侵入したのです......"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:40
msgid ""
"In the early summer of 1095 YW, the Ha’atel brothers were sent to an outpost "
"in Wesnoth called the Stone of Erzen; Gwiti had mixed feelings about Nati, "
"who had followed him to become an army physician. At the same time, however, "
"he was somewhat concerned by Nati’s occasional suspicious behavior and his "
"unusual and vast knowledge of magic.\n"
"\n"
"Then, one day, an incident occurred that will forever be etched in the "
"memory for Gwiti: the great band of the northern orcs launched their night "
"raid against the Stone of Erzen. Their mighty and merciless incursion "
"decimated the fortress guards in one night. The battlefield was stained red "
"with blood, and dead soldiers lay scattered across the ground. It was in "
"this moment that Gwiti experienced true fear for the first time."
msgstr ""
"Wesnoth 歴 1095 年の初夏、Ha’atel 兄弟は Erzen の石と呼ばれる Wesnoth の前哨"
"基地へ派遣されました。Gwiti は自らを追って軍医となった Nati に対し、複雑な感"
"情を抱いていました。しかし、同時に、Nati が時折見せる不審な行動や、異様なまで"
"の、そして膨大な彼の魔法の知識に、若干の懸念を覚えざるを得ませんでした。\n"
"\n"
"そしてある日、Gwiti にとって永遠に記憶に残るであろう事件が起こりました。北方"
"のオークの大軍勢が Erzen の石に対して夜襲を仕掛けたのです。彼らの強大で、情け"
"を知らない侵略によって、要塞の衛兵達は一夜にして壊滅しました。戦場は血によっ"
"て赤く染まり、辺りには犠牲となった兵士達が倒れていました。Gwiti はこの時初め"
"て、本当の恐怖を体験しました。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:45
msgid ""
"However, Gwiti was saved from the depths of despair in what he did not "
"expect: the screams and cries of the orcish warriors echoing across the "
"battlefield. What Gwiti witnessed was Nati raising their fallen comrades "
"from the brink of death, commanding them as undead soldiers, and causing "
"them to fight once more. The battlefield, with its mishmash of corpses, "
"skeletons, and souls, had transformed into nothing short of the hellish "
"nightmare. The orcs, overcome with fear and confusion, quickly fell into "
"disarray, and the tide of the battle turned."
msgstr ""
"しかし Gwiti は、彼にとって全く予想外の形で、絶望の底から救われました。それ"
"は、戦場に鳴り響くオークの戦士達の悲鳴、そして断末魔でした。Gwiti が目にした"
"のは、Nati が、かつての味方を死の淵から蘇らせ、不死の兵士として操り、戦わせて"
"いる光景でした。死体や骸骨、魂が入り乱れた戦場は、控えめに言っても地獄絵図と"
"化していました。オーク達は恐怖と混乱に陥り、一気に戦局は逆転しました。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:49
msgid ""
"Gwiti was intensely upset and then recalled his concern for Nati. In fact, "
"Nati had been corrupted by his pursuit of knowledge from the tome. In the "
"end, however, Gwiti summoned the undead with Nati and gave them their "
"orders. In other words, at the last minute, he trusted Nati again as his "
"brother. In Gwiti’s eyes, it was obvious that Nati had degenerated into "
"irredeemable evil. And yet, he leaned on him, choosing to stand alongside "
"him. After all, Gwiti realized anew that Nati was the only family he had "
"left in this world."
msgstr ""
"Gwiti は激しく動揺した後、Nati に対する彼の懸念を思い出しました。実際、Nati "
"はあの書物の知識の追求に身を埋め、堕落していたのでした。しかし結局、Gwiti は "
"Nati と共にアンデッドを召還し、彼らに命令を与えました。言い換えれば、彼はこの"
"土壇場で、Nati を再び兄として信じたのです。Gwiti の目には、Nati が救いようが"
"ない邪悪へ堕落している事は明らかでした。それでも、彼は Nati に頼り、行動を共"
"にしました。Gwiti は、もはや地上に残された肉親が Nati だけである事を再認識し"
"たからです。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:53
msgid ""
"However, their actions were both forbidden and reckless. Amidst the chaos, "
"the cavalry reinforcements arriving at Erzen collided not with the orcs, but "
"with the undead summoned by the brothers. The battle devolved into "
"uncontrolled carnage, with no distinction between friend and foe. What "
"followed was long and harrowing stretch of relentless violence, until Erzen "
"was reduced to ruins. Nothing remained but rubble and countless casualties. "
"Realizing that his forces were facing defeat, Nati abandoned Gwiti and fled, "
"leaving his brother behind."
msgstr ""
"しかし彼らの行動は禁じ手であり、軽率でもありました。混乱の渦中で、援軍として "
"Erzen へ到着した騎兵隊が、オークではなく、兄弟の呼び出したアンデッドと衝突し"
"たのです。戦いは敵味方の区別もつかぬまま繰り広げられました。それから長く、凄"
"惨な時間がただひたすら過ぎた後、Erzen は廃墟と化し、瓦礫と犠牲のみが残りまし"
"た。Nati は自らの勢力が敗北を喫していると感じ、Gwiti を一人捨てて逃走しまし"
"た。"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:57
msgid ""
"Isolated and alone, Gwiti was captured as an enemy of the Kingdom. During "
"his torture, he desperately cried out for Nati’s name. The Ha’atel brothers’ "
"reunion would come at the moment of their judgment. The people of Wesnoth, "
"terrified of their magic, decided to condemn them to the fate of certain "
"death: banishment to the sea, where they would be left to drown. Mercy was "
"not an option. The same people who had once respected them as physicians now "
"mocked and despised them.\n"
"\n"
"Naturally, Gwiti began to harbor growing hatred and rage toward those still "
"living. But for Nati, consumed by the curse of the tome, such thoughts no "
"longer occurred. Even when ordered by soldiers, he refused to let go of the "
"book, clinging to it desperately, earning only looks of contempt and "
"resignation from those around him."
msgstr ""
"孤立した Gwiti は王国の敵として捕らえられました。彼は裁きを受けている間、必死"
"で Nati の名を叫びました。Ha’atel 兄弟の再会は、彼らに与えられた最後の時でし"
"た。Wesnoth の人々は彼らの魔法を恐れ、確実に破滅させるべく、海へ追放し、溺死"
"させる事に決めたのです。誰も彼らに慈悲は与えませんでした。それまで彼らを医者"
"として尊敬していた人々が、彼らを侮蔑し、嫌悪し始めたのです。\n"
"\n"
"当然の事ながら、Gwiti はそんな人々、生きている者達に対しての憎しみと怒りを育"
"て始めました。しかし、書の呪いに染まった Nati には、もはやそんな発想すら浮か"
"びませんでした。彼は兵士から命令されても、書を決して手放そうとせず、人々から"
"蔑みと諦めの目で眺められていました。"

#. [part]
#. [scenario]: id=01_A_New_Chance
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:63
#: The_Dark_Hordes/scenarios/01_A_New_Chance.cfg:5
msgid "A New Chance"
msgstr "新たな凶兆"

#. [part]
#: The_Dark_Hordes/macros/storytxt.cfg:64
msgid ""
"The two were placed aboard the rotting, rudderless ship and cast toward the "
"sea, their passage meant to end in death. However, the Lady of Fate herself "
"intervened with them. A sudden storm engulfed the vessel carrying Gwiti and "
"Nati. The ship was torn apart, and the brothers were swallowed by the "
"furious waves, separated amidst the chaos. Gwiti’s cries echoed through the "
"storm before they were silenced. Eventually, each brother washed ashore on "
"separate lands. Not even Gwiti could have known that this was the beginning "
"of the Rise of the Dark Hordes..."
msgstr ""
"二人は朽ち果てた、舵のない船に乗せられました。そして、死に繋がる海へ向かって"
"送り出されました。しかし、運命を司る女神は、彼らに介入しました。突然の嵐が、"
"Gwiti と Nati を乗せた船を襲ったのです。船はバラバラに分解し、兄弟は荒波に飲"
"まれ、離れ離れになりました。Gwiti の叫び声だけが嵐の中で轟いていました。そし"
"て彼らは最終的に、それぞれ別々の陸地へ漂着を遂げたのです。これこそが暗黒の大"
"軍団の蜂起の始まりである事を、Gwiti すらも知りませんでした......"

